</head>
<body>

  <div class="container" id="doc-content">
    <h1><i class="fa-solid fa-house"></i> CozyStay ‚Äì Full Stack Rental Listing Web Application</h1>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>üîß Tech Stack</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Backend:</strong> Node.js, Express.js</li>
        <li><strong>Frontend:</strong> EJS (Embedded JavaScript), Bootstrap 5, Font Awesome</li>
        <li><strong>Database:</strong> MongoDB Atlas (cloud-hosted)</li>
        <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> Passport.js (with sessions)</li>
        <li><strong>Cloud Storage:</strong> Cloudinary (for images) with Multer</li>
        <li><strong>Maps Integration:</strong> Mapbox (for interactive location display)</li>
        <li><strong>Deployment:</strong> Render</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>üìå Project Overview</h2>
      <p>
        CozyStay is a full-featured rental listing platform where users can create, explore, and review accommodation listings. 
        It includes secure user authentication, map-based location viewing, image uploads, and CRUD functionality for listings and reviews.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>‚úÖ Key Features</h2>

      <h3>User Authentication & Authorization</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Registration, login, logout using Passport.js</li>
        <li>Session-based login with secure route protection</li>
        <li>Only listing/review owners can edit or delete their own content</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>CRUD Operations</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Users can create, update, and delete listings and reviews</li>
        <li>Server-side validation and user-friendly error handling</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Image Uploads</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Integrated Cloudinary for image hosting</li>
        <li>Handled uploads via Multer middleware</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Map Integration</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Integrated Mapbox to display listing locations on an interactive map</li>
        <li>Geocoding used to convert address input into coordinates</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Middleware Usage</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><code>isLoggedIn</code>: Protects routes from unauthenticated access</li>
        <li><code>isOwner</code>: Ensures only owners can modify/delete listings</li>
        <li><code>validateListing</code> and <code>validateReview</code>: Custom validation logic</li>
        <li><code>express-mongo-sanitize</code> and <code>helmet</code>: For security</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Responsive UI</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Built with Bootstrap 5 to ensure a clean, mobile-friendly interface</li>
        <li>Font Awesome icons for modern design aesthetics</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Deployment</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Deployed on Render</li>
        <li>Environment variables managed securely via <code>.env</code> file</li>
        <li>MongoDB Atlas used as the production database</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>üîê Security Measures</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><code>helmet</code> for setting secure HTTP headers</li>
        <li><code>express-mongo-sanitize</code> to prevent NoSQL injection</li>
        <li>Flash messages for feedback and user experience</li>
        <li>Input validation to prevent invalid or malicious data</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <button class="download-btn" onclick="downloadPage()">üì• Download This Page</button>
  </div>

  <script>
    function downloadPage() {
      const element = document.createElement("a");
      const html = document.documentElement.outerHTML;
      const file = new Blob([html], { type: 'text/html' });
      element.href = URL.createObjectURL(file);
      element.download = "CozyStay_Project_Documentation.html";
      document.body.appendChild(element);
      element.click();
      document.body.removeChild(element);
    }
  </script>
</body>
</html>
